&quot;Hey, are you guys ready for two?&quot; he asks.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sure.. bring 'em&quot; replied Thor, Cann'ing down as I'm healing him with my Donal's arms over and over again. My manastone doesn't work here and this is as close to &quot;free mana&quot; as we can get here.<br>
<br>
&quot;Inc&quot;<br>
<br>
I'm sitting down, literally watching my mana bar rise... oh.... so.... slowly. I see Gordy's life bar drop a bit as he wings around the left corner and enters the room. &quot;How about four?&quot; he asks comically. Just then a small swarm of nasty skels comes pouring out of the left hunting area. Dad and Gordy immediately jump into action, taking down the first skell a full bubble before it knows what hit it. Gim lines up a backstab and starts plunging his daggers into the undead's ass for big hits while G's and Dad's swords are shredding it. Thor, Nand and I are in the background, pulling the other skels away from the primary one and &quot;ghetto mezzing&quot; them (root parking) in different corners of the room. Thor slows them and as he aggros, we root them in place and concentrate on the one being beaten on. <br>
<br>
Life bars swing up and down while mana and swords explode upon the skeletons' bony faces. One down... second one is about to drop from Nan's &quot;see ya, wouldn't wanna BE ya&quot; nukes. <br>
<br>
&quot;All Snared.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;All Slowed.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;All Karn'ed.&quot;<br>
<br>
Sweet. Now it's just up to the melee folks to finish off the battle while the mana folks sit and relax a bit, reapplying an occasional Root here and there. Dad and Gordy are side by side, putting SUCH a beating on the skels that you almost feel sorry for them. Almost. Gim's on the opposite side, hitting them with Hasted daggers and doing some serious damage. Soon, all four skels are down. I think I could count on two hands the number of words spoken during battle. It was more art than science. We even had time to emote a few funny things and use foul language with the MOBs. AND.. my XP bar moved up a notch. Damn, I'm proud to work with these guys.<br>
<br>
Now that the first big pull was done, I figured it was time to tell them what I purposely avoided mentioning until we got settled down..<br>
<br>
&quot;Gents.. good job all around! And just so that you all know.. I've *never* heard of this place being done WITHOUT an enchanter.&quot; <br>
<br>
You should have heard the silence. &lt;lol&gt; I was sitting at my computer laughing out loud! Gim says &quot;Maybe you should have told us that before we came down here...&quot; <br>
<br>
I replied &quot;Hell no.. that would have changed the way you would have done things.&quot; <br>
<br>
As it turned out, we did pretty well except for a couple of overpulls which resulted in just one death (Thor went running for the zone and then remembered that we had an Evac'er with us - - he did a 180 and tried to make it back but ran out of fuel, having to ditch in the water tunnel) but we were back in action a very short time later. If we had more room to operate, we could have parked them far enough apart to be able to handle six easily, but that damned room is *so* small. &lt;grin&gt;<br>
<br>
At one point, brave little Gordy caught a little extra aggro on a long-range pull and watching his life bar plummet I asked, &quot;You want a heal or should I let you die and avoid aggro?&quot;<br>
<br>
Without missing a beat, Thorab hits the keyboard with machine-gun speed...<br>
<br>
&quot;Let him die.&quot;<br>
&quot;Let him die.&quot;<br>
&quot;Let him die.&quot; over and over again.. about 20 times. It was VERY funny. <br>
<br>
I ignored The Great Stinkini's (our nickname for the big stanky barbarian) requests and threw some mana into a wounded Gordy. He returned to the group with what looked like the Undead Frickin' Brady Bunch in tow. Six... seven... eight skells come cascading down the ramp of the right pull area. Dang. THAT is a lotta skels. Nan's already on his feet with his finger mashing down the Evac button. Now its just a matter of dumping mana fast enough to keep them aggroed OFF of Nan while the evac spell completes.<br>
<br>
Dad and Gordy are taunting their little hearts out and I'm group healing, trying to draw fire away from Nan and onto my thick armor as the nine evac seconds pass by *impossibly* slow. I'm almost on fumes when I see the &quot;You have created a portal&quot; message. Whew!! Safe!! <br>
<br>
At that point it was getting late and we all decided to camp. It's best to leave on a good note. &lt;wink&gt;<br>
<br>
Needless to say, a good time was had by all.<br>
<br>
Daku Inochi<br>
